Description:

Imagine you're queuing at a post office and you request a turn number. Turns have 5 types:
- C (Prior appointment)
- E (Sending)
- R (Pickup)
- O (Other procedures)
- I (Information)
They also have a consecutive number, so they look like:
- C024
- E001
- C025
- R123
The numbers must be consecutive per turn type (each type has its own counter).
Build a structure that:
- Creates a new turn
- Calls the person who has that turn
- Deletes the turn once it's been attended
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Program:

To try this program, just run: "php YourFileDirectory/PostalOrder.php" on the terminal! To quit the program, just press ctrl + c on the terminal.